27/09/2005
TIRANA, Albania -- The British embassy in Tirana issued a statement Monday (26 September) warning British citizens who intend to travel in Albania to consider security risks in some areas of the country.
According to the statement, cited by the daily Albanian News on Tuesday (27 September), the embassy particularly mentioned northeast border areas between Albania and Kosovo.
Recently, a bus carrying some 30 passengers -- including three British tourists -- from Tirana to Shkodra was stopped by an armed gang and robbed.
(Albanian News - 27/09/05)
